For product versions and upgrade paths, see the [Product Compatibility Matrix](http://docs.pivotal.io/compatibility-matrix.pdf).

## <a id="220"></a>v2.2.0

**Release Date:**  January XX, 2018

* This version of the MySQL for PCF can only be installed in an Ops Manager v1.12 or later environment.

* MySQL for PCF v2.2.0 offers the ability to create multi-AZ leader-follower instances. Operators can monitor leader-follower
  instances with replication metrics.
  For more information, see [About Leader-Follower](./about-leader-follower.html).

* The MySQL for PCF tile no longer includes the option to disable automated backups. 
  You must configure automated backups. 
  For more information, see [Backing Up and Restoring On-Demand MySQL for PCF](backup-and-restore.html). 

* MySQL for PCF v2.2.0 updates the mysql-restore utility to make restoring from a backup artifact easier.
  For more information, see [Restore the Service Instance](./backup-and-restore.html#restoreinstance).

* MySQL for PCF v2.2.0 adds the ability to enable create service binding and service keys with custom usernames.
  For more information, see [Customizing Database Credentials](./customize-access.html).

* MySQL for PCF v2.2.0 enables developers to use workload profiles for best practices in server configuration.
  For more information, see [Changing MySQL Server Defaults](./change-default.html).

* MySQL for PCF no longer includes individual errand VMs. 
  Instead, errands are run on the MySQL VMs. 
  Errands now run faster and use fewer resources. 

* MySQL for PCF v2.2.0 upgrades several dependencies including, `golang 1.9.1`.

